<section id="slide-org5f6aeb9">
<div class="slide-header">Evaluating CAS for teaching & learning: Alasdair McAndrew, ATCM2017</div>
<h2 id="org5f6aeb9">A hybrid model: FACTIONS!</h2>
<table border="2" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="6" rules="groups" frame="hsides">


<colgroup>
<col  class="org-left" />

<col  class="org-left" />
</colgroup>
<thead>
<tr>
<th scope="col" class="org-left">Criterion</th>
<th scope="col" class="org-left">Meaning</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td class="org-left">Functionality, or fitness for purpose</td>
<td class="org-left">Must manage all mathematics in the course</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td class="org-left">Access</td>
<td class="org-left">by all students, at all times</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td class="org-left">Cost</td>
<td class="org-left">initial purchase, deployment, upkeep, maintenance, licencing&#x2026;</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td class="org-left">Teaching &amp; Learning</td>
<td class="org-left">&#xa0;</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td class="org-left">Interactivity and user-friendliness</td>
<td class="org-left">Must fit the needs of the <i>students</i> more than the <i>teacher</i></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td class="org-left">Organizational issues</td>
<td class="org-left">Fit in with current policies and practices</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td class="org-left">Novelty</td>
<td class="org-left">Should be seen as something new and exciting</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td class="org-left">Students</td>
<td class="org-left">Different cohorts require difference approaches, and possibly different software</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>

</section>
